**Hydration là gì?**
- Server render HTML → Client nhận HTML → React "hydrate" để make interactive
- Attach event listeners
- Reconcile server HTML với client React tree

**Process**:
```
1. Server renders HTML string
2. Browser displays HTML (fast first paint)
3. JavaScript loads
4. React hydrates: attaches to existing DOM
5. App becomes interactive
```

**Hydration Mismatch**:
- Server và client render khác nhau
- React logs warning và re-renders
- Performance penalty

**Common causes**:
```tsx
// 1. Date/time
<p>Current time: {new Date().toISOString()}</p>
// Server: "2024-01-01T10:00:00"
// Client: "2024-01-01T10:00:01"

// 2. window/localStorage
<p>Theme: {localStorage.getItem('theme')}</p>
// Server: undefined
// Client: "dark"

// 3. Math.random()
<div key={Math.random()}>...</div>
```

**Fixes**:
```tsx
// 1. useEffect for client-only
const [time, setTime] = useState<string>();
useEffect(() => {
  setTime(new Date().toISOString());
}, []);

// 2. suppressHydrationWarning
<time suppressHydrationWarning>{date}</time>

// 3. Next.js dynamic import với ssr: false
const ClientOnlyComponent = dynamic(
  () => import('./ClientComponent'),
  { ssr: false }
);

// 4. useIsClient hook
function useIsClient() {
  const [isClient, setIsClient] = useState(false);
  useEffect(() => setIsClient(true), []);
  return isClient;
}
```

**Next.js 14+ Suspense boundaries**:
```tsx
<Suspense fallback={<Skeleton />}>
  <ClientOnlyContent />
</Suspense>
```

**Keys giúp React**:
- Identify elements qua re-renders
- Efficient reconciliation
- Preserve component state

**Wrong key = Wrong state**:
```tsx
// Bug: Using index as key với reorderable list
{items.map((item, index) => (
  <TodoItem key={index} item={item} />
))}

// Scenario:
// Before: [A, B, C] with indices [0, 1, 2]
// Delete A: [B, C] with indices [0, 1]
// React thinks: item at index 0 changed from A to B
// Result: B gets A's state!
```

**Correct key usage**:
```tsx
// Use stable, unique identifier
{items.map((item) => (
  <TodoItem key={item.id} item={item} />
))}
```

**Index as key is OK when**:
- List is static (never reorders)
- Items have no state
- Items are never deleted/inserted

**Force remount với key**:
```tsx
// Reset component state when user changes
<UserProfile key={userId} userId={userId} />

// Reset form
<Form key={formKey} />
<button onClick={() => setFormKey(k => k + 1)}>Reset</button>
```

**Debugging tip**:
```tsx
// Check for duplicate keys
const ids = items.map(i => i.id);
const hasDuplicates = ids.length !== new Set(ids).size;
```

**Anti-patterns**:
```tsx
// Bad: Random key = remount every render
key={Math.random()}

// Bad: Non-unique key
key={item.category}  // Multiple items same category

// Bad: Concatenating non-unique values
key={`${item.name}-${index}`}  // Still depends on index
```

**Cleanup chạy khi**:
1. Trước effect chạy lại (dependencies changed)
2. Khi component unmounts

```tsx
useEffect(() => {
  console.log('Effect runs');
  return () => {
    console.log('Cleanup runs');
  };
}, [dep]);

// Sequence khi dep changes:
// 1. Cleanup (old effect)
// 2. Effect (new)
```

**Common leaks và fixes**:

1. **Subscriptions**:
```tsx
// Leak
useEffect(() => {
  socket.on('message', handleMessage);
}, []);

// Fixed
useEffect(() => {
  socket.on('message', handleMessage);
  return () => socket.off('message', handleMessage);
}, []);
```

2. **Timers**:
```tsx
useEffect(() => {
  const id = setInterval(tick, 1000);
  return () => clearInterval(id);
}, []);
```

3. **Fetch requests**:
```tsx
useEffect(() => {
  const controller = new AbortController();

  fetch('/api/data', { signal: controller.signal })
    .then(res => res.json())
    .then(setData)
    .catch(err => {
      if (err.name !== 'AbortError') throw err;
    });

  return () => controller.abort();
}, []);
```

4. **Event listeners**:
```tsx
useEffect(() => {
  const handler = (e) => { ... };
  window.addEventListener('resize', handler);
  return () => window.removeEventListener('resize', handler);
}, []);
```

**Stale closure issue**:
```tsx
// Bug: Logs stale count
useEffect(() => {
  const id = setInterval(() => console.log(count), 1000);
  return () => clearInterval(id);
}, []); // count not in deps

// Fix: Add dependency or use ref
useEffect(() => {
  const id = setInterval(() => console.log(count), 1000);
  return () => clearInterval(id);
}, [count]);
```

**Circular Dependency là gì?**
- Module A imports Module B
- Module B imports Module A
- JavaScript không thể resolve

**NestJS forwardRef**:
```ts
// user.module.ts
@Module({
  imports: [forwardRef(() => PostModule)],
  providers: [UserService],
  exports: [UserService],
})
export class UserModule {}

// post.module.ts
@Module({
  imports: [forwardRef(() => UserModule)],
  providers: [PostService],
  exports: [PostService],
})
export class PostModule {}
```

**Service-level forwardRef**:
```ts
@Injectable()
export class UserService {
  constructor(
    @Inject(forwardRef(() => PostService))
    private postService: PostService,
  ) {}
}
```

**Better: Restructure để avoid circular**:

1. **Extract shared module**:
```ts
// shared.module.ts
@Module({
  providers: [SharedService],
  exports: [SharedService],
})
export class SharedModule {}

// Both UserModule and PostModule import SharedModule
```

2. **Use events**:
```ts
// Instead of direct call
this.postService.notifyUser(userId);

// Emit event
this.eventEmitter.emit('post.created', { userId, postId });

// Handle in UserModule
@OnEvent('post.created')
handlePostCreated(payload) { ... }
```

3. **Dependency Inversion**:
```ts
// Define interface in shared module
interface IUserService {
  findById(id: string): Promise<User>;
}

// Inject by token
@Inject('IUserService') private userService: IUserService
```

**Prevention**:
- Clear module boundaries
- Unidirectional dependencies
- Shared modules for common functionality
- Event-driven communication

