**useState** — Triggers re-render:
```tsx
const [count, setCount] = useState(0);
setCount(1); // Component re-renders
```

**useRef** — No re-render:
```tsx
const countRef = useRef(0);
countRef.current = 1; // No re-render
```

**Khi dùng useRef**:

1. **DOM references**:
```tsx
const inputRef = useRef<HTMLInputElement>(null);
<input ref={inputRef} />
inputRef.current?.focus();
```

2. **Mutable values không cần re-render**:
```tsx
const intervalRef = useRef<number>();

useEffect(() => {
  intervalRef.current = setInterval(() => {
    // Do something
  }, 1000);
  return () => clearInterval(intervalRef.current);
}, []);
```

3. **Previous value tracking**:
```tsx
function usePrevious<T>(value: T): T | undefined {
  const ref = useRef<T>();
  useEffect(() => {
    ref.current = value;
  });
  return ref.current;
}
```

4. **Avoiding stale closures**:
```tsx
const callbackRef = useRef(callback);
useEffect(() => {
  callbackRef.current = callback;
});

useEffect(() => {
  const id = setInterval(() => {
    callbackRef.current(); // Always latest callback
  }, 1000);
  return () => clearInterval(id);
}, []); // No dependency needed
```

**So sánh**:
| Feature | useState | useRef |
|---------|----------|--------|
| Re-render | Yes | No |
| Persists | Yes | Yes |
| Sync | Async (batched) | Sync |
| Use case | UI state | Mutable values, DOM |

**Rule of thumb**: Nếu value không cần hiển thị trong UI, dùng useRef.

**useCallback** — Memoize function:
```tsx
const handleClick = useCallback(() => {
  doSomething(id);
}, [id]);
```

**useMemo** — Memoize value:
```tsx
const sortedItems = useMemo(() => {
  return items.sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name));
}, [items]);
```

**Khi THỰC SỰ cần**:

1. **Pass callback to memoized child**:
```tsx
const handleDelete = useCallback((id) => {
  deleteItem(id);
}, [deleteItem]);

<MemoizedList onDelete={handleDelete} />
```

2. **Expensive computations**:
```tsx
const filtered = useMemo(() => {
  return items.filter(complexFilter).map(complexTransform);
}, [items]);
```

3. **Dependency of useEffect**:
```tsx
const options = useMemo(() => ({ page, limit }), [page, limit]);

useEffect(() => {
  fetchData(options);
}, [options]);
```

**Khi KHÔNG cần** (premature optimization):

```tsx
// Bad - simple calculation
const doubled = useMemo(() => count * 2, [count]);

// Bad - function not passed to memoized child
const handleClick = useCallback(() => {
  setCount(c => c + 1);
}, []);
<button onClick={handleClick}>Click</button>  // button not memoized

// Bad - reference equality không matter
const style = useMemo(() => ({ color: 'red' }), []);
<div style={style}>  // inline object cũng OK
```

**Rule of Thumb**:
- Measure first với React DevTools Profiler
- useMemo cho expensive calculations
- useCallback khi passing to React.memo children
- Don't memoize everything by default

**Algorithms**:

1. **Token Bucket**:
```ts
class TokenBucket {
  private tokens: number;
  private lastRefill: number;

  constructor(
    private capacity: number,
    private refillRate: number // tokens per second
  ) {
    this.tokens = capacity;
    this.lastRefill = Date.now();
  }

  tryConsume(): boolean {
    this.refill();
    if (this.tokens >= 1) {
      this.tokens -= 1;
      return true;
    }
    return false;
  }

  private refill() {
    const now = Date.now();
    const elapsed = (now - this.lastRefill) / 1000;
    this.tokens = Math.min(this.capacity, this.tokens + elapsed * this.refillRate);
    this.lastRefill = now;
  }
}
```

2. **Sliding Window Log**:
```ts
class SlidingWindowLog {
  private requests: number[] = [];

  constructor(
    private windowMs: number,
    private maxRequests: number
  ) {}

  tryConsume(): boolean {
    const now = Date.now();
    const windowStart = now - this.windowMs;

    // Remove old requests
    this.requests = this.requests.filter(t => t > windowStart);

    if (this.requests.length < this.maxRequests) {
      this.requests.push(now);
      return true;
    }
    return false;
  }
}
```

**Redis Implementation**:
```ts
async function checkRateLimit(userId: string): Promise<boolean> {
  const key = `rate:${userId}`;
  const limit = 100;
  const window = 60; // seconds

  const current = await redis.incr(key);
  if (current === 1) {
    await redis.expire(key, window);
  }

  return current <= limit;
}
```

**Distributed Rate Limiting**:
```ts
// Sliding window counter with Redis
async function slidingWindowCounter(userId: string): Promise<boolean> {
  const now = Date.now();
  const windowSize = 60000; // 1 minute
  const limit = 100;

  const currentWindow = Math.floor(now / windowSize);
  const previousWindow = currentWindow - 1;
  const currentKey = `rate:${userId}:${currentWindow}`;
  const previousKey = `rate:${userId}:${previousWindow}`;

  const [current, previous] = await redis.mget(currentKey, previousKey);
  const weight = (now % windowSize) / windowSize;
  const count = (parseInt(previous) || 0) * (1 - weight) + (parseInt(current) || 0);

  if (count >= limit) return false;

  await redis.incr(currentKey);
  await redis.expire(currentKey, windowSize * 2 / 1000);
  return true;
}
```

